# Supabase Rules

Supabase is the main data layer.

All Supabase calls must live in services.

Example:
features/cards/services/cards.service.ts

Queries must:

- filter in the database
- select only needed columns
- limit results

Example:

supabase
  .from('cards')
  .select('id,title,created_at')
  .eq('user_id', userId)
  .limit(20)

Realtime should only be used when necessary.

All tables must enforce Row Level Security (RLS).

Never expose the service_role key in the frontend.
Use only the anon key.